Soy MP Caleb Kositany and his Kapseret counterpart Oscar Sudi arrive at Rift Valley Regional DCI Headquarters in Nakuru to record statements over the Friday violence targeting ODM Leader Raila Odinga in Uasin Gishu County where a helicopter was stoned. [Harun Wathari, Standard]  Members of Parliament for Soy and Kapseret Caleb Kositany and Oscar Sudi have presented themselves at the Rift Valley Regional Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) Headquarters in Nakuru.  The duo was summoned yesterday over their alleged role in the stoning of Raila Odinga’s chopper.  DCI, in a statement yesterday said investigations into the incident suggested the MPs had a role in planning the chaos.   Ploce said that at the closure of the ceremony, chaos erupted with stones and other projectiles being hurled at Raila by incited youth, damaging his helicopter’s windscreen. The incident occurred on Friday evening during the burial of Mzee Jackson Kibor at his Kabenes home in Soy Sub-County, Uasin Gishu County.  More to follow….    By Irissheel Shanzu | 4 hours ago By Peterson Githaiga and Victor Nzuma | 4 hours ago By Mkamburi Mwawasi | 5 hours ago By Daniel Chege | 5 hours ago